attributes.action: Vote against the Assisted Dying Bill
attributes.additional_details: We urge the UK Government to reject the Assisted Dying Bill and instead prioritize initiatives that improve palliative care, mental health support, and resources for those experiencing end-of-life challenges. These alternatives could ensure dignity and support. I believe that relying on implementing assisted dying instead places vulnerable people at risk and does not uphold our societal commitment to valuing life.
attributes.background: I would like MPs to vote against the Terminally Ill Adults (End of Life) Bill. I believe it sets a dangerous precedent, devaluing life based on contribution, not inherent worth. I think it undermines our core principles & puts doctors in a conflicted position, challenging their oath to protect life.
